Author:
Vol / Page: 13
Edition:
Quote: <i>Camp oven</i>. An iron pot with three short legs and a flat top, so that it can be used to boil, bake, or fry in. It is a convenient utensil but heavy to carry and awkward to pack on a horse. (C.)
Notes: Acland Glossary

