Author: OWEN & PERKINS
Vol / Page: 153
Edition:
Quote: On the ground in front of the fire would be the great camp ovens; these were twenty-four inches wide and eight or nine inches deep, standing on short legs. Coals of fire were shovelled under the camp oven or poured on top to give the necessary heat. And that's where the cook did his baking.
Notes:

